es to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"shown on the map. The shapes may be instances of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","isActive":true},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","isActive":true},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or they may be defined by local or external","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"GeoJSON","type":"text"},{"text":" code. A shape source is added to an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle","isActive":true},{"text":" object along with an ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle","isActive":true},{"text":" object. The vector style","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"layer defines the appearance of any content supplied by the shape source. You","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can update a shape source by setting its ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shape"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URL"},{"text":" property.","type":"text"}],"title":"MLNShapeSource","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnshapesource","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNStyle":{"abstract":[{"text":"The proxy object for the current map style.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MLNStyle","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNStyle"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnstyle"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNShapeSourceOptionMaximumZoomLevelForClustering":{"abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeV